Defendant Erica Lynn Froehlich in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Ct 1.  State will move to dismiss Ct 2.  Atty Gumz agrees  Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 1.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made freely, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 1.  Ct 2 is ordered dismissed.
Counsel make sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:
Ct 1:  *Pay base fine of $75.00 plus costs for a total of $418.38 (which includes drug abuse surcharge)
*Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge of $200.00
*Court grants expungement under 973.015 after 12 months, upon request by defendant, if all fines/costs are paid in full and there are no other criminal violations.

*Bond on file to be applied.
